```php
function safe_file_download($filename) {
    // Define allowed extensions
    $allowed_extensions = ['mp3', 'wav'];

    // Get directory where audio files are stored
    $base_dir = __DIR__ . '/audio_files/';

    // Sanitize input filename
    $filename = basename($filename);

    // Check if file extension is allowed
    $extension = pathinfo($filename, PATHINFO_EXTENSION);
    if (!in_array(strtolower($extension), $allowed_extensions)) {
        die("Invalid file type.");
    }

    // Construct full file path
    $file_path = $base_dir . $filename;

    // Verify that the file is within the base directory
    if (strpos(realpath($file_path), realpath($base_dir)) !== 0) {
        die("File not found or access denied.");
    }

    // Check if file exists
    if (!file_exists($file_path)) {
        die("File does not exist.");
    }

    // Set headers and send the file
    header('Content-Type: application/octet-stream');
    header('Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="' . basename($file_path) . '"');
    header('Expires: 0');
    header('Cache-Control: must-revalidate');
    header('Pragma: public');
    header('Content-Length: ' . filesize($file_path));
    readfile($file_path);
}

// Example usage:
safe_file_download($_GET['filename']);
```

This script ensures that only files with specific extensions located in a predefined directory can be downloaded. It also verifies that the requested file path does not traverse out of the intended directory, thus preventing arbitrary file reads.

